			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				From my childhood days, I developed a keen interest in being a generalist and building
				businesses that make a difference, and I embarked on multiple side hustles. After
				graduating, I stumbled upon my first job offer at an Ed Tech startup called HeyMath! in
				Chennai as a Software Engineer. It was there that I realized the gap between being college
				smart and possessing the actual skills required as a software developer in the business
				world to make production-ready code. After gaining sufficient knowledge in the early years
				of my career, I started volunteering as the Campus Connect Chair for a couple of
				non-profits, educating students across colleges in South India. Along with my team, we
				organized various campus programs, events, workshops, and hackathons to bridge the skill
				gaps between the curriculum and real-world tech stacks. Additionally, I was part of the
				managing team for two technology user groups in Chennai: the Adobe Flex User Group and the
				HTML User Group, where we organized events, sessions, hackathons, and provided training to
				the developer community on the latest technology trends.
			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				In 2012, I joined Report Bee, an Education Data Analytics company, as a founding team
				member. As the Head of Engineering, I worked closely with the founders and CTO to build the
				tech team and develop the product from the ground up. In 2018, XSEED Education acquired
				Report Bee. My time with Report Bee allowed me to understand the education landscape across
				the world and collaborate with various experts from governments and publishers such as
				Pearson and Oxford along with building world class robust tech products and teams.
			</p>
			<p class='text-muted-foreground'>
				In 2019, I decided to take a break from formal work to bond with my family. During the next
				3 years, we visited 7 countries, relocated to the US for my wife's research, and I became
				the dad of two amazing boys. Along with all these, I founded Collabwrite, a consulting
				agency, through which I explored my passion to build and solve growth problems. Collabwrite
				provided me with opportunities to work with several founders and leaders on their challenges
